00:20:37.019 --> 00:20:42.649
We know Facebook, Twitter, now Google+ is
just one more thing to keep us distracted

00:20:42.649 --> 00:20:44.049
in the day.

00:20:44.049 --> 00:20:47.460
Everyone, email, IM, text message, everyone
is struggling with this.

00:20:47.460 --> 00:20:53.669
I don't know anyone who's not struggling with
issues of attention during their workday.

00:20:53.669 --> 00:20:59.889
And if you take two people who have roughly
the same educational credentials, roughly

00:20:59.889 --> 00:21:05.659
the same training, technical knowledge, same
background, and one of them has a fantastic

00:21:05.659 --> 00:21:08.259
attention and just gets to work.

00:21:08.259 --> 00:21:09.559
They've got a clear mind.

00:21:09.559 --> 00:21:10.559
They're focused.

00:21:10.559 --> 00:21:15.059
They can get right to work and not be distracted
and they're going throughout the day with

00:21:15.059 --> 00:21:18.830
a great level of energy and focus and attention.

00:21:18.830 --> 00:21:25.169
And you compare that to your typical corporate
worker, who is drinking three or four cups

00:21:25.169 --> 00:21:30.179
of coffee just to get awake in the morning,
get started, gets distracted by all these

00:21:30.179 --> 00:21:34.809
social media things, doesn't really know where
they're going in a workday, maybe has to have

00:21:34.809 --> 00:21:39.249
another huge jolt of caffeine in the afternoon
just to get through the day.

00:21:39.249 --> 00:21:45.430
You compare those two people and the first
person I mentioned is gonna win in a career

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:47.009
ten times out of ten.

00:21:47.009 --> 00:21:53.289
So, that's again another type of investing
in your human capital that is highly leveraged

00:21:53.289 --> 00:21:55.580
in that it doesn't take a lot of money.

00:21:55.580 --> 00:21:56.840
This is stuff you can learn about.

00:21:56.840 --> 00:22:02.309
You can focus on your time and your money
and your attention and you can change yourself.

00:22:02.309 --> 00:22:04.099
And we can all change ourselves this way.

00:22:04.099 --> 00:22:06.769
And it has a huge impact on our careers.

00:22:06.769 --> 00:22:16.450
And if you think again about productivity
is being labor times capital, you all have

00:22:16.450 --> 00:22:20.239
a certain amount of labor that you're bringing
to the table here.

00:22:20.239 --> 00:22:21.779
Eight, ten, twelve hours a day.

00:22:21.779 --> 00:22:25.720
I don't know quite how much all of you are
spending each day, but it's a fixed amount.

00:22:25.720 --> 00:22:30.580
So, we're talking about changing things in
ourselves that makes each of those minutes

00:22:30.580 --> 00:22:33.330
you bring to the table more productive.

00:22:33.330 --> 00:22:37.539
And that ends up in bringing much, much higher
career results.

00:22:37.539 --> 00:22:40.950
So, there's a lot of ways to focus on attention.

00:22:40.950 --> 00:22:43.840
I just saw a wonderful sign there about meditation.

