00:52:01.460 --> 00:52:08.380
The name comes from the Pomodoro kitchen timers,
those tomatoes that you twist and it tick-tocks

00:52:08.380 --> 00:52:10.130
in the kitchen.

00:52:10.130 --> 00:52:14.950
And the idea is that it's basically a timer
and you can get digital versions of this.

00:52:14.950 --> 00:52:18.119
That goes for 25 minutes.

00:52:18.119 --> 00:52:25.609
And in 25 minutes, you focus on one thing
and you turn off all the email and the notifications

00:52:25.609 --> 00:52:28.619
and the Facebook and the Google+ and all these
things.

00:52:28.619 --> 00:52:30.849
You focus on one thing for 25 minutes.

00:52:30.849 --> 00:52:32.240
The timer goes off.

00:52:32.240 --> 00:52:34.790
You get a five minute break and you can do
whatever you want.

00:52:34.790 --> 00:52:36.060
You can go and get tea.

00:52:36.060 --> 00:52:37.680
You can make some cell phone calls.

00:52:37.680 --> 00:52:39.180
You can check your Facebook.

00:52:39.180 --> 00:52:40.920
Then the timer goes off in five minutes.

00:52:40.920 --> 00:52:43.109
You go back to 25.

00:52:43.109 --> 00:52:45.240
That cycle, they call it a Pomodoro.

00:52:45.240 --> 00:52:48.170
